test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 26 == -26
 +  where 26 = <built-in function prod>([-2, -13])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 0 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7472385c0740>([-26])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7472385c0740> = [[1, -26], [-26], [1, -26], [-26], [1, -26], [-26]].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7472385c0740>([1, -26])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7472385c0740> = [[1, -26], [-26], [1, -26], [-26], [1, -26], [-26]].count
 +  and   0 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7472385c0740>([-26, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7472385c0740> = [[1, -26], [-26], [1, -26], [-26], [1, -26], [-26]].count
